td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Wanna PvP?  Read and Learn (EDIT 11/29)</span><hr size=1> My name is Acillatem Zoso.<br>
<br>
I am a level 55 Wizard on Tallon Zek, and spend about 95% of my free time (non raids etc) PKing solo.<br>
<br>
My resists, self buffed are as follows:<br>
<br>
PR - 167<br>
MR - 121<br>
DR - 147<br>
FR - 182<br>
CR - 166<br>
<br>
<br>
INT is 170 - PLENTY of mana IMO.  I can kill 3 casters on a full bar of mana, and have about 20-40% left after killing a melee (well sometimes run oom, depending on fight heh)<br>
<br>
<br>
Anywayz buffs.<br>
<br>
Here's the order plain and simple.  <br>
<br>
Shifting Sight (on yourself)<br>
Heat Sight<br>
Chill Sight<br>
Resistant Skin<br>
Elemental Armor<br>
See invis<br>
Manasink<br>
Shield of the Magi (or equivalent)<br>
Barrier of Force (or equivalent)<br>
Shield of Lava<br>
SHM Dmg shield potion<br>
Levitate<br>
Jboots/SoW potion<br>
<br>
<br>
Remove Heat Sight and Shifting Sight after buffing.  This gives u 2 open slots for DoTs.<br>
<br>
Annul Magic will remove Splurt, Winged Death, Engulfing Line, Snare, Root, Ignite Blood line (Pyrocure), Vexing Mordania, Malo, etc etc  Prolly missing a few but it's like 3 AM here heh.  Pretty much anything that DOESNT have a poison or disease symbol, with the exception of Tashania, can be removed with Annul Magic.<br>
<br>
Spells I keep memmed:<br>
<br>
Harvest<br>
Shock of Lightning, Snare, or Tears (usually have Tears up)<br>
Lure or Ice Comet (usually have Lure up)<br>
Draught of Fire<br>
Immobilize (root whatever u use)<br>
Yonder<br>
Gate<br>
Annul Magic (this is my &quot;floating&quot; spell slot - switch out buffs)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Miscellaneous Tips</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
On PvP servers, you can forget spells like root or snare against players.   People's MR is usually 100+ and that just don't fly.  You are WASTING your time UNLESS you are fighting someone at least 5 levels below you.  Even then its hard to get root to stick.<br>
<br>
If you can, carry Cure Poison/Dis potions - they work on all  DoT's as well as Enchanter's Tashani line (Tash line is Poison based if u didn't know).<br>
<br>
Remember that spells only do 2/3 damage in PvP.  So your Ice Comet is only doing about 775 damage to a player, not 1120.<br>
<br>
Carry some Golem Metal wands for those druids/shaman/clerics.<br>
<br>
Get some Complete-Heal potions off Ishva in Paw, or purchase some Stinging Wort potions off a SHM (expensive tho)..<br>
<br>
Soulfire......did u know ANY class can use the Complete Heal ability off of Soulfire?  I love that trick <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
Know the class yer fighting - plain and simple.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Pet owners</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Pets - root them, then snare them, then forget them.<br>
<br>
Smart pet owners will annul your roots.  This can be a problem, just keep rooting them tho.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Necros</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
<br>
For the most part do 1 of two things.<br>
<br>
Chain Lifetap or Dump DoTs on you then Lifetap.<br>
<br>
Remember that lifetaps do NOT supercede Barrier of Force or Manaskin.  It WILL damage it - but unless they take life from you, they will not gain life.  USe this to your advantage.<br>
<br>
Their DoTs usually take time to start taking effect.  You can use this time to either annul, or nuke.  Your choice.  I usually will Annul just in case, but if I only need one more nuke for the kill, I'll deal with the DoT later.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Shaman and Druids</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
<br>
dont bother with your Draught line - you are wasting your time.<br>
<br>
Draught - 3.0 sec does 440 damage in PvP unresisted.<br>
<br>
Sham and Dru at 55+ get chloroblast - 3.0 sec 450 heal.<br>
<br>
So at BEST you are doing 440 damage and that is if it is totally unresisted.  Solution?  Ice Comet and Tears.  May be slow - but what usually happens is I open with Ice Comet (or two until I get that one that lands and hits hard), and now they are at 25-30% health in mid cast of either a nuke or DoT.  Slip in that Draught of Fire and u usually have yourself a kill - if not go with Ice Comet again.  You will have time to get off the Draught + IC maybe 2 secs before they get that second chloroblast if you catch them in mid cast as described above.  <br>
<br>
Ice Comet/Tears line is the key to any healing class.  Otherwise they can EASILY outheal you becuz of the PvP nerf to our spells.<br>
<br>
If a shaman hits u with Inciduous Decay do NOT cure it - all it is is a DR debuff......wait for the actual DoT then use yer potion.<br>
<br>
Golem wands are VERY important for shaman and druids.  For shaman they don't quite serve the greatest purpose (removing SoW) becuz most at 50+ have SoW boots.<br>
<br>
But druids that lose ALL those nice buffs USUALLY panic and click Spirit of Cheetah.  This is when that 4th charge comes in handy.  If u see them SoC, u &quot;click&quot; the wand and u now have a helpless druid.  A lot of druids/shaman/rangers do NOT have Jboots.  So u now have a sitting duck.  Nuke away.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Enchanters</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Chanters are iffy.  Depends on pets/timing/resisting mez.  But if they get u mezzed and start mana draining you/cripple etc...ugh it sux.  And as you sit there watching your mana drop from 90% to 10% - your only options become Yonder/Gate lol (been there, done that).  If you have 150+ MR tho, ENC are easy, even if you do get Tashed.<br>
<br>
If yer lucky enough tho and they are stupid enough u can slide in 3 nukes for the kill.  Smart chanters will re-apply Rune after each mez.  Chanters usually have real crappy resists as they are overly concerned with INT AND CHA - resists are like not important to them.  I recommend Draughts - fast (needed to compete with mez) and decent dmg output.<br>
<br>
59+ chanters get Rapture tho - VERY hard to get around that.  But it can be doen - remember the golem wands and fast cast nukes.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Warriors</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Levi is important, and this is why its one of your last buffs.  You lose levi/SoW, you are pretty much dead meat if u get caught in a valley etc and lose Yonder as an option.  At 50+ true warriors are tough becuz u hafta do the yonder/nuke game.  They usually have MR thru the roof becuz their primary concern is NOT to be rooted/snared.  <br>
<br>
Fungis suck - plain and simple.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Rogues/Monks</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Best advice here is Damage shield potions.  Yonder/Lure works good, but usually not good enough.  The dmg shield stacked with Manaskin etc is a great combo that gets them to at LEAST 2/3 life before Epic rune breaks.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Paladins</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Pallies are pretty damn hard to beat.  They heal - have an assload of hitpoints, and if they have LoH up u might as well just gate.  <br>
<br>
The ONLY solution I can come up with for Paladins is to blind them.  This means Bio Orbs.  If they cant see their life, they can know when to heal.  <br>
<br>
Otherwise it's almost a losing battle unless u are lvl 60 and even then I'd imagine its tough.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Clerics</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Another dificult opponent.  Golem wands + nuke + Tears would work.  Again tho - they can EASILY outheal you.  If a cleric just sits and goes defensive - forget it yer wasting yer time.  Heals dont have a 66% nerf.<br>
<br>
But if u come up on a cleric who thinks he can outnuke you, you might have a chance.  Slim at best tho.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Rangers</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Key here is golem wands.  Get rid of their hp buffs, their SoW, their atk buffs etc.  Use Lures - drop them to about 33% and they start to heal - Tears comes in handy.<br>
<br>
Rangers are difficult - but this tactic has worked int he past for me.  Again, dmg shield potions are KEY for rangers as well.  I can't stress enough the use of Shaman made Dmg Shield potions, and if u have the cash - Ro's Breath.  They stack, its a 65 point dmg shield.  It hurts simply put.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Mages</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Mages can be difficult ONLY if they just sit there and annul the root on their pets.  Otherwise u can easily kill them.  If u run across an epic pet, my best advice would be to golem wand it once, then root it.  Otherwise they will be buffed out the yin yang making it near impossible to root.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Wizards</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Simply put?  Lure.  This was how at 54 I beat a lvl 60 wiz.  Golem wand to strip all his buffs then Lure. <br>
<br>
The golem wand gave me the upper edge by essentially removing Manasink (200) + epic rune (800) + Shield of the Magi (280).  So in essence I just dropped the amount of damage I would need to do by 1300 (or 3 Lures).<br>
<br>
Anywayz I'm falling asleep now - any questions just ask.  Any comments feel free to share - I'm sure I left out some things as it is very late - but I'm bored and thought I'd share my 2cp with ya.<br>
<br>
PvP for wizards has ups and downs depending on spell levels.  But overall I'd say from 44 on we are kings of PvP.<br>
<br>
<br>
